## Phase 1: Security & Infrastructure Foundation

Everything starts with security. No financial platform survives without it.

### [NEW] `backend/middleware/auth.js`
- **JWT authentication** — access tokens (15min) + refresh tokens (7d)
- **Password hashing** — bcrypt with salt rounds 12
- **Session management** — token blacklist for logout
- **Role-based access** — `user`, `admin`, `auditor`
- User login with email/password or wallet signature

### [NEW] `backend/middleware/rateLimiter.js`
- Per-IP rate limiting (100 req/min general, 10 req/min for auth)
- Per-user rate limiting for financial operations (5 orders/sec)
- DDoS protection with sliding window

### [NEW] `backend/middleware/validator.js`
- Input sanitization on ALL endpoints (prevent SQL injection, XSS)
- Schema validation for every request body (type checking, bounds)
- File upload validation (magic bytes, not just extension)

### [NEW] `backend/middleware/audit.js`
- Logs EVERY state-changing API call with: who, what, when, from where, request body, response code
- Tamper-proof audit log (hashed chain — each entry hashes the previous)
- Separate audit database table with forensic detail

### [NEW] `backend/config/security.js`
- CORS configuration (whitelist origins)
- Helmet.js headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame, etc.)
- Request size limits
- Secure cookie settings

### [MODIFY] `database.js`
Expand to **25+ tables** with proper foreign keys, indexes, and constraints:

**New tables:**
