## Phase 4: Asset Lifecycle Management

### [NEW] `backend/services/assetService.js`

Full lifecycle with state machine:

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> draft: Create
    draft --> documents_uploaded: Upload Docs
    documents_uploaded --> ai_analyzing: Trigger AI
    ai_analyzing --> verified: AI Approved
    ai_analyzing --> rejected: AI Rejected
    rejected --> draft: Re-edit
    verified --> compliance_review: Auto-check
    compliance_review --> active: Passed
    compliance_review --> flagged: Issues Found
    flagged --> active: Admin Override
    active --> funding: First Investment
    funding --> funded: 100% Tokens Sold
    funding --> expired: Deadline Passed
    funded --> payout_pending: Auto-trigger
    payout_pending --> completed: Payout Done
    expired --> refunding: Auto-trigger
    refunding --> closed: All Refunded
```

**Escrow System:**
- Each asset gets a dedicated escrow address on the blockchain
- Coins locked in escrow when tokens are purchased
- Escrow releases ONLY when: (a) fully funded → to owner, or (b) expired → refund to investors
- Double-entry bookkeeping — every movement has a debit and credit

**Compliance Checks:**
- Raise amount limits (configurable)
- Maximum exposure per investor (can't put > X% of portfolio in one asset)
- Cooling-off period after listing (24h before investments open)
- Mandatory description length and document requirements

### [NEW] `backend/services/escrowService.js`
- Create escrow accounts per asset
- Lock/unlock funds
- Auto-release on conditions met
- Refund processing on expiry

### [NEW] `backend/services/complianceService.js`
- Pre-listing compliance checks
- Investor exposure limits
- Transaction monitoring
- Suspicious activity reports

